4 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 4.1-02-12 of the North Dakota Century Code is
5 amended and reenacted as follows:
6 4.1-02-12. Assessment.
7 An assessment at the rate of twentythirty mills per bushel [35.24 liters] is imposed upon all
8 barley grown in this state, delivered to this state, or sold to a first purchaser in this state. The
9 assessment does not apply to barley grown by a producer and used by the producer as
10 livestock feed.
11 SECTION 3. AMENDMENT. Section 4.1-13-15 of the North Dakota Century Code is
12 amended and reenacted as follows:
13 4.1-13-15. Assessment.
14 An assessment at the rate of fifteentwenty mills per bushel [35.24 liters] by weight is
15 imposed upon all wheat:
16 1. All wheat grownGrown in this state, at the time of its sale;
17 2. All wheat deliveredDelivered into this state, at the time of its sale; and
18 3. All wheat soldSold through commercial channels to a first purchaser in this state.
